# Local Server

Luna runs as a **single server** on port 3000. It serves both the API and the built UI from `ui/dist/`.

| Service | Port | URL | Start command |
|---------|------|-----|---------------|
| Luna (API + UI) | 3000 | http://localhost:3000 | `.venv/bin/luna serve --port 3000` |

## UI Build — MANDATORY before every server start

The server serves pre-built static files from `ui/dist/`. There is NO Vite dev server, NO hot-reload. Every time you change any UI file (`.tsx`, `.ts`, `.css`, anything under `ui/src/`), you MUST rebuild before the change is visible:

```bash
cd ui && npm run build
```

**If you skip this step, the user sees stale UI.** This is the #1 source of "nothing changed" complaints.

## Restart procedure

Always rebuild UI, kill the existing process, then start fresh:

```bash
# 1. Rebuild UI (ALWAYS do this)
cd ui && npm run build

# 2. Kill + restart server
lsof -ti:3000 | xargs kill -9 2>/dev/null; sleep 1
.venv/bin/luna serve --port 3000
```

Never use a different port. If the port is occupied, kill the occupant.

## OAuth redirect URIs

All OAuth plugins derive redirect URIs from the server's origin. With the single-server setup on port 3000, all callbacks are:

- Google: `http://localhost:3000/api/p/plugin-google-auth/callback`
- Slack: `http://localhost:3000/api/p/plugin-slack/callback`
- Monday: `http://localhost:3000/api/p/plugin-monday/callback`

These must be registered in each provider's OAuth app settings. Never change the port without updating the provider configs.
